criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Male or female with intact uterus and at least one ovary

          -  Aged of 18 to 75 years old;

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Pregnancy or lactation women;

          -  Presence of pituitary/hypothalamic disorders, polycystic ovarian syndrome or other
             endocrinal and metabolic disorders that known to compromise
             hypothalamic-pituitary-gonadal function;

          -  Receiving psychotropic or hormonal medications including hormonal contraception and
             hormone therapies;

          -  Taking lipid-lowering agents or hypoglycemic agents and other drugs that known to
             influence cardiovascular health;

          -  Obviously poor compliance.
